The Super Eagles of Nigeria at the weekend, secured a place in the round of 16 of the ongoing Africa Cup of Nations, Cameroon 2021 with a 3-1 win over the Jediane Falcons of Sudan in Group D.  Samuel Chukwueze provided an early goal at the Roumdé Adjia Stadium in Garoua, which gave a positive start for the three-time champions. Afterwards, Taiwo Awoniyi got their second on the stroke of half-time, while Moses Simon slotted in the third goal just 30 seconds into the second half. Sudan were lucky to pull a goal back with a penalty converted by Walieldin Khedr - but it wasn’t enough as the team lost the game. Nigeria have now secured six points from their opening two games, after beating Egypt on Tuesday, while Sudan have just one point. Nigeria will next play Guinea Bissau from 8pm on Wednesday (January 19th) while Egypt and Sudan will lock horns in Yaounde, same time and day.